kubevirt's approach looks good, but right now our DC spec stores 1 OS -> 1 image for openstack, while kubevirt has 1 OS -> multiple versions -> 1 image per version. I'd rather not touch the DC spec of openstack for this.

The support ticket just wants a dropdown of project-scoped images instead of the one preset image. my ddea is adding a field in kubermaticsettings that, when enabled, makes the dashboard API fetch images from openstack. machine-controller already does something similar here: https://github.com/kubermatic/machine-controller/blob/c87c24541364de60e0e4cf8cae3a184f82a2a102/pkg/cloudprovider/provider/openstack/provider.go#L545-L549

for example, we can have sth like the following:

user picks an OS in the wizard or node deployment editor.
frontend calls the dashboard API image endpoint with the selected OS and the user's OpenStack credentials.
dashboard API fetches all images visible in the user's project. OpenStack has no server-side OS filter, so we fetch everything and filter ourselves.
keep only the images whose os_distro matches the selected OS.
If nothing matches os_distro, return only dc.spec.openstack.images[os].

frontend renders those as a dropdown, with dc.spec.openstack.images[os] marked as the default.
If the OS changes, the frontend calls again. The API serves from cache if warm, else re-fetches.




So, i checked that os_distro is an optional metadata and often missing. On setups where images aren't tagged, the dropdown just shows the datacenter default. That's expected, not a bug and we can document it. we can cache the full list for about 5 minutes and filter per OS in memory. We run multiple replicas with no shared cache, so a cold replica just re-fetches which should be fine. and then we can filter based on status=active  and os_distro (edited) 
